  "prompt": "If any unknown person complaint FIR (not name in FIR) against me then what I should do?",
  "response": "If an FIR (First Information Report) is filed against you by an unknown person without mentioning your name specifically, here are some steps you should consider:\n\n1. Seek Legal Advice\n- Consult a criminal lawyer immediately\n- Get professional guidance on handling the situation\n- Understand your legal rights and potential implications\n\n2. Gather Information\n- Try to obtain a copy of the FIR\n- Understand the nature of the complaint\n- Identify the details of the alleged incident\n\n3. Do Not Ignore the Complaint\n- Ignoring an FIR can lead to legal complications\n- Respond appropriately through legal channels\n\n4. Document Everything\n- Collect all relevant documents and evidence\n- Maintain a record of your whereabouts and activities\n- Prepare a detailed timeline if possible\n\n5. Cooperate with Investigation\n- Be prepared to provide statements\n- Do not obstruct the investigation\n- Remain calm and professional\n\n6. Potential Legal Actions\n- File a counter-complaint if false allegations are made\n- Request proper investigation\n- Seek anticipatory bail if necessary\n\n7. Stay Calm and Composed\n- Do not make hasty decisions\n- Avoid direct confrontation\n- Let your lawyer handle communication\n\nAlways consult a qualified legal professional for personalized advice specific to your situation.",
